{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So historically there has"},{"time":2000,"text":"been a huge divide between what people"},{"time":5000,"text":"consider to be non-living systems on one"},{"time":8000,"text":"side, and living systems on the other side."},{"time":10000,"text":"So we go from, say, this beautiful and"},{"time":12000,"text":"complex crystal as non-life, and this rather"},{"time":15000,"text":"beautiful and complex cat on the other side."},{"time":18000,"text":"Over the last hundred and fifty years or so,"},{"time":21000,"text":"science has kind of blurred this distinction"},{"time":23000,"text":"between non-living and living systems, and"},{"time":25000,"text":"now we consider that there may be a kind"},{"time":27000,"text":"of continuum that exists between the two."},{"time":30000,"text":"We'll just take one example here:"},{"time":32000,"text":"a virus is a natural system, right?"},{"time":34000,"text":"But it's very simple. It's very simplistic."},{"time":36000,"text":"It doesn't really satisfy all the requirements,"},{"time":38000,"text":"it doesn't have all the characteristics"},{"time":40000,"text":"of living systems and is in fact a parasite"},{"time":42000,"text":"on other living systems in order to, say,"},{"time":45000,"text":"reproduce and evolve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"But what we're going to be talking about here"},{"time":49000,"text":"tonight are experiments done on this sort of"},{"time":51000,"text":"non-living end of this spectrum -- so actually"},{"time":53000,"text":"doing chemical experiments in the laboratory,"},{"time":56000,"text":"mixing together nonliving ingredients"},{"time":58000,"text":"to make new structures, and that these"},{"time":60000,"text":"new structures might have some of the"},{"time":62000,"text":"characteristics of living systems."},{"time":64000,"text":"Really what I'm talking about here is"},{"time":66000,"text":"trying to create a kind of artificial life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"So what are these characteristics that I'm"},{"time":70000,"text":"talking about? These are them."},{"time":72000,"text":"We consider first that life has a body."},{"time":74000,"text":"Now this is necessary to distinguish the self"},{"time":76000,"text":"from the environment."},{"time":78000,"text":"Life also has a metabolism. Now this is a"},{"time":80000,"text":"process by which life can convert resources"},{"time":83000,"text":"from the environment into building blocks"},{"time":85000,"text":"so it can maintain and build itself."},{"time":88000,"text":"Life also has a kind of inheritable information."},{"time":90000,"text":"Now we, as humans, we store our information"},{"time":92000,"text":"as DNA in our genomes and we pass this"},{"time":95000,"text":"information on to our offspring."},{"time":97000,"text":"If we couple the first two -- the body and the metabolism --"},{"time":99000,"text":"we can come up with a system that could"},{"time":101000,"text":"perhaps move and replicate, and if we"},{"time":103000,"text":"coupled these now to inheritable information,"},{"time":106000,"text":"we can come up with a system that would be"},{"time":108000,"text":"more lifelike, and would perhaps evolve."},{"time":110000,"text":"And so these are the things we will try to do"},{"time":112000,"text":"in the lab, make some experiments that have"},{"time":114000,"text":"one or more of these characteristics of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"So how do we do this? Well, we use"},{"time":119000,"text":"a model system that we term a protocell."},{"time":121000,"text":"You might think of this as kind of like a"},{"time":123000,"text":"primitive cell. It is a simple chemical"},{"time":125000,"text":"model of a living cell, and if you consider"},{"time":128000,"text":"for example a cell in your body may have"},{"time":130000,"text":"on the order of millions of different types"},{"time":132000,"text":"of molecules that need to come together,"},{"time":134000,"text":"play together in a complex network"},{"time":136000,"text":"to produce something that we call alive."},{"time":139000,"text":"In the laboratory what we want to do"},{"time":141000,"text":"is much the same, but with on the order of"},{"time":143000,"text":"tens of different types of molecules --"},{"time":145000,"text":"so a drastic reduction in complexity, but still"},{"time":147000,"text":"trying to produce something that looks lifelike."},{"time":150000,"text":"And so what we do is, we start simple"},{"time":152000,"text":"and we work our way up to living systems."},{"time":155000,"text":"Consider for a moment this quote by"},{"time":157000,"text":"Leduc, a hundred years ago, considering a"},{"time":159000,"text":"kind of synthetic biology:"},{"time":161000,"text":"\"The synthesis of life, should it ever occur,"},{"time":163000,"text":"will not be the sensational discovery which we"},{"time":165000,"text":"usually associate with the idea.\""},{"time":167000,"text":"That's his first statement. So if we actually"},{"time":169000,"text":"create life in the laboratories, it's"},{"time":171000,"text":"probably not going to impact our lives at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"\"If we accept the theory of evolution, then"},{"time":175000,"text":"the first dawn of synthesis of life must consist"},{"time":177000,"text":"in the production of forms intermediate"},{"time":179000,"text":"between the inorganic and the organic"},{"time":181000,"text":"world, or between the non-living"},{"time":183000,"text":"and living world, forms which possess"},{"time":185000,"text":"only some of the rudimentary attributes of life\""},{"time":187000,"text":"-- so, the ones I just discussed --"},{"time":189000,"text":"\"to which other attributes will be slowly added"},{"time":191000,"text":"in the course of development by the"},{"time":193000,"text":"evolutionary actions of the environment.\""},{"time":195000,"text":"So we start simple, we make some structures"},{"time":197000,"text":"that may have some of these characteristics"},{"time":199000,"text":"of life, and then we try to develop that"},{"time":201000,"text":"to become more lifelike."},{"time":203000,"text":"This is how we can start to make a protocell."},{"time":205000,"text":"We use this idea called self-assembly."},{"time":207000,"text":"What that means is, I can mix some"},{"time":209000,"text":"chemicals together in a test tube in my lab,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and these chemicals will start to self-associate"},{"time":213000,"text":"to form larger and larger structures."},{"time":215000,"text":"So say on the order of tens of thousands,"},{"time":217000,"text":"hundreds of thousands of molecules will"},{"time":219000,"text":"come together to form a large structure"},{"time":221000,"text":"that didn't exist before."},{"time":223000,"text":"And in this particular example,"},{"time":225000,"text":"what I took is some membrane molecules,"},{"time":227000,"text":"mixed those together in the right environment,"},{"time":229000,"text":"and within seconds it forms these rather"},{"time":231000,"text":"complex and beautiful structures here."},{"time":233000,"text":"These membranes are also quite similar,"},{"time":235000,"text":"morphologically and functionally,"},{"time":237000,"text":"to the membranes in your body,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and we can use these, as they say,"},{"time":241000,"text":"to form the body of our protocell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"Likewise,"},{"time":244000,"text":"we can work with oil and water systems."},{"time":246000,"text":"As you know, when you put oil and water together,"},{"time":248000,"text":"they don't mix, but through self-assembly"},{"time":250000,"text":"we can get a nice oil droplet to form,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and we can actually use this as a body for"},{"time":254000,"text":"our artificial organism or for our protocell,"},{"time":256000,"text":"as you will see later."},{"time":258000,"text":"So that's just forming some body stuff, right?"},{"time":260000,"text":"Some architectures."},{"time":262000,"text":"What about the other aspects of living systems?"},{"time":264000,"text":"So we came up with this protocell model here"},{"time":266000,"text":"that I'm showing."},{"time":268000,"text":"We started with a natural occurring clay"},{"time":270000,"text":"called montmorillonite."},{"time":272000,"text":"This is natural from the environment, this clay."},{"time":274000,"text":"It forms a surface that is, say, chemically active."},{"time":276000,"text":"It could run a metabolism on it."},{"time":278000,"text":"Certain kind of molecules like to associate"},{"time":280000,"text":"with the clay. For example, in this case, RNA, shown in red"},{"time":282000,"text":"-- this is a relative of DNA,"},{"time":284000,"text":"it's an informational molecule --"},{"time":286000,"text":"it can come along and it starts to associate"},{"time":288000,"text":"with the surface of this clay."},{"time":290000,"text":"This structure, then, can organize the"},{"time":292000,"text":"formation of a membrane boundary around"},{"time":294000,"text":"itself, so it can make a body of"},{"time":296000,"text":"liquid molecules around itself, and that's"},{"time":298000,"text":"shown in green here on this micrograph."},{"time":300000,"text":"So just through self-assembly, mixing things"},{"time":302000,"text":"together in the lab, we can come up with, say,"},{"time":305000,"text":"a metabolic surface with some"},{"time":307000,"text":"informational molecules attached"},{"time":309000,"text":"inside of this membrane body, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"So we're on a road towards living systems."},{"time":315000,"text":"But if you saw this protocell, you would not"},{"time":317000,"text":"confuse this with something that was actually alive."},{"time":319000,"text":"It's actually quite lifeless. Once it forms,"},{"time":321000,"text":"it doesn't really do anything."},{"time":323000,"text":"So, something is missing."},{"time":325000,"text":"Some things are missing."},{"time":327000,"text":"So some things that are missing is,"},{"time":329000,"text":"for example, if you had a flow of energy"},{"time":331000,"text":"through a system, what we'd want"},{"time":333000,"text":"is a protocell that can harvest"},{"time":335000,"text":"some of that energy in order to maintain itself,"},{"time":337000,"text":"much like living systems do."},{"time":339000,"text":"So we came up with a different protocell"},{"time":341000,"text":"model, and this is actually simpler than the previous one."},{"time":343000,"text":"In this protocell model, it's just an oil droplet,"},{"time":345000,"text":"but a chemical metabolism inside"},{"time":347000,"text":"that allows this protocell to use energy"},{"time":349000,"text":"to do something, to actually become dynamic,"},{"time":352000,"text":"as we'll see here."},{"time":354000,"text":"You add the droplet to the system."},{"time":356000,"text":"It's a pool of water, and the protocell"},{"time":358000,"text":"starts moving itself around in the system."},{"time":360000,"text":"Okay? Oil droplet forms"},{"time":362000,"text":"through self-assembly, has a chemical"},{"time":364000,"text":"metabolism inside so it can use energy,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and it uses that energy to move itself"},{"time":368000,"text":"around in its environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"As we heard earlier, movement is very"},{"time":372000,"text":"important in these kinds of living systems."},{"time":374000,"text":"It is moving around, exploring its environment,"},{"time":376000,"text":"and remodeling its environment, as you see,"},{"time":378000,"text":"by these chemical waves that are forming by the protocell."},{"time":380000,"text":"So it's acting, in a sense, like a living system"},{"time":382000,"text":"trying to preserve itself."},{"time":385000,"text":"We take this same moving protocell here,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and we put it in another experiment,"},{"time":390000,"text":"get it moving. Then I'm going"},{"time":392000,"text":"to add some food to the system,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and you'll see that in blue here, right?"},{"time":397000,"text":"So I add some food source to the system."},{"time":399000,"text":"The protocell moves. It encounters the food."},{"time":401000,"text":"It reconfigures itself and actually then"},{"time":403000,"text":"is able to climb to the highest concentration"},{"time":405000,"text":"of food in that system and stop there."},{"time":407000,"text":"Alright? So not only do we have this system"},{"time":409000,"text":"that has a body, it has a metabolism,"},{"time":411000,"text":"it can use energy, it moves around."},{"time":414000,"text":"It can sense its local environment"},{"time":416000,"text":"and actually find resources"},{"time":418000,"text":"in the environment to sustain itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"Now, this doesn't have a brain, it doesn't have"},{"time":422000,"text":"a neural system. This is just a sack of"},{"time":424000,"text":"chemicals that is able to have this interesting"},{"time":426000,"text":"and complex lifelike behavior."},{"time":428000,"text":"If we count the number of chemicals"},{"time":430000,"text":"in that system, actually, including the water"},{"time":432000,"text":"that's in the dish, we have five chemicals"},{"time":434000,"text":"that can do this."},{"time":436000,"text":"So then we put these protocells together in a"},{"time":438000,"text":"single experiment to see what they would do,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and depending on the conditions, we have"},{"time":442000,"text":"some protocells on the left that are"},{"time":444000,"text":"moving around and it likes to touch the other"},{"time":446000,"text":"structures in its environment."},{"time":448000,"text":"On the other hand we have two moving"},{"time":450000,"text":"protocells that like to circle each other,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and they form a kind of a dance, a complex dance with each other."},{"time":454000,"text":"Right? So not only do individual protocells"},{"time":456000,"text":"have behavior, what we've interpreted as"},{"time":458000,"text":"behavior in this system, but we also have"},{"time":460000,"text":"basically population-level behavior"},{"time":463000,"text":"similar to what organisms have."},{"time":466000,"text":"So now that you're all experts on protocells,"},{"time":469000,"text":"we're going to play a game with these protocells."},{"time":471000,"text":"We're going to make two different kinds."},{"time":473000,"text":"Protocell A has a certain kind of chemistry"},{"time":476000,"text":"inside that, when activated, the protocell"},{"time":478000,"text":"starts to vibrate around, just dancing."},{"time":480000,"text":"So remember, these are primitive things,"},{"time":482000,"text":"so dancing protocells, that's very"},{"time":484000,"text":"interesting to us. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"The second protocell has a different"},{"time":488000,"text":"chemistry inside, and when activated,"},{"time":490000,"text":"the protocells all come together and they fuse"},{"time":492000,"text":"into one big one. Right?"},{"time":494000,"text":"And we just put these two together"},{"time":496000,"text":"in the same system."},{"time":498000,"text":"So there's population A,"},{"time":500000,"text":"there's population B, and then"},{"time":502000,"text":"we activate the system,"},{"time":504000,"text":"and protocell Bs, they're the blue ones,"},{"time":506000,"text":"they all come together. They fuse together"},{"time":508000,"text":"to form one big blob, and the other protocell"},{"time":510000,"text":"just dances around. And this just happens"},{"time":512000,"text":"until all of the energy in the system is"},{"time":514000,"text":"basically used up, and then, game over."},{"time":517000,"text":"So then I repeated this experiment"},{"time":519000,"text":"a bunch of times, and one time"},{"time":521000,"text":"something very interesting happened."},{"time":523000,"text":"So, I added these protocells together"},{"time":525000,"text":"to the system, and protocell A and protocell B"},{"time":527000,"text":"fused together to form a hybrid protocell AB."},{"time":529000,"text":"That didn't happen before. There it goes."},{"time":531000,"text":"There's a protocell AB now in this system."},{"time":534000,"text":"Protocell AB likes to dance around for a bit,"},{"time":537000,"text":"while protocell B does the fusing, okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"But then something even more interesting happens."},{"time":543000,"text":"Watch when these two large protocells,"},{"time":545000,"text":"the hybrid ones, fuse together."},{"time":547000,"text":"Now we have a dancing protocell"},{"time":550000,"text":"and a self-replication event. Right. (Laughter)"},{"time":554000,"text":"Just with blobs of chemicals, again."},{"time":556000,"text":"So the way this works is, you have"},{"time":558000,"text":"a simple system of five chemicals here,"},{"time":560000,"text":"a simple system here. When they hybridize,"},{"time":562000,"text":"you then form something that's different than"},{"time":564000,"text":"before, it's more complex than before,"},{"time":566000,"text":"and you get the emergence of another kind of"},{"time":568000,"text":"lifelike behavior which"},{"time":570000,"text":"in this case is replication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"So since we can make some interesting"},{"time":574000,"text":"protocells that we like, interesting colors and"},{"time":576000,"text":"interesting behaviors, and they're very easy"},{"time":578000,"text":"to make, and they have interesting lifelike"},{"time":580000,"text":"properties, perhaps these protocells have"},{"time":583000,"text":"something to tell us about the origin of life"},{"time":585000,"text":"on the Earth. Perhaps these represent an"},{"time":587000,"text":"easily accessible step, one of the first steps"},{"time":589000,"text":"by which life got started on the early Earth."},{"time":592000,"text":"Certainly, there were molecules present on"},{"time":594000,"text":"the early Earth, but they wouldn't have been"},{"time":596000,"text":"these pure compounds that we worked with"},{"time":598000,"text":"in the lab and I showed in these experiments."},{"time":600000,"text":"Rather, they'd be a real complex mixture of"},{"time":602000,"text":"all kinds of stuff, because"},{"time":604000,"text":"uncontrolled chemical reactions produce"},{"time":606000,"text":"a diverse mixture of organic compounds."},{"time":608000,"text":"Think of it like a primordial ooze, okay?"},{"time":611000,"text":"And it's a pool that's too difficult to fully"},{"time":613000,"text":"characterize, even by modern methods, and"},{"time":615000,"text":"the product looks brown, like this tar here"},{"time":617000,"text":"on the left. A pure compound"},{"time":619000,"text":"is shown on the right, for contrast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"So this is similar to what happens when you"},{"time":623000,"text":"take pure sugar crystals in your kitchen,"},{"time":625000,"text":"you put them in a pan, and you apply energy."},{"time":627000,"text":"You turn up the heat, you start making"},{"time":629000,"text":"or breaking chemical bonds in the sugar,"},{"time":631000,"text":"forming a brownish caramel, right?"},{"time":633000,"text":"If you let that go unregulated, you'll"},{"time":635000,"text":"continue to make and break chemical bonds,"},{"time":637000,"text":"forming an even more diverse mixture of"},{"time":639000,"text":"molecules that then forms this kind of black"},{"time":641000,"text":"tarry stuff in your pan, right, that's"},{"time":643000,"text":"difficult to wash out. So that's what"},{"time":645000,"text":"the origin of life would have looked like."},{"time":647000,"text":"You needed to get life out of this junk that"},{"time":649000,"text":"is present on the early Earth,"},{"time":651000,"text":"four, 4.5 billion years ago."},{"time":653000,"text":"So the challenge then is,"},{"time":655000,"text":"throw away all your pure chemicals in the lab,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and try to make some protocells with lifelike"},{"time":659000,"text":"properties from this kind of primordial ooze."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"So we're able to then see the self-assembly"},{"time":664000,"text":"of these oil droplet bodies again"},{"time":666000,"text":"that we've seen previously,"},{"time":668000,"text":"and the black spots inside of there"},{"time":670000,"text":"represent this kind of black tar -- this diverse,"},{"time":672000,"text":"very complex, organic black tar."},{"time":674000,"text":"And we put them into one of these"},{"time":676000,"text":"experiments, as you've seen earlier, and then"},{"time":678000,"text":"we watch lively movement that comes out."},{"time":680000,"text":"They look really good, very nice movement,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and also they appear to have some kind of"},{"time":684000,"text":"behavior where they kind of circle"},{"time":686000,"text":"around each other and follow each other,"},{"time":689000,"text":"similar to what we've seen before -- but again,"},{"time":691000,"text":"working with just primordial conditions,"},{"time":693000,"text":"no pure chemicals."},{"time":695000,"text":"These are also, these tar-fueled protocells,"},{"time":697000,"text":"are also able to locate resources"},{"time":699000,"text":"in their environment."},{"time":700000,"text":"I'm going to add some resource from the left,"},{"time":702000,"text":"here, that defuses into the system,"},{"time":704000,"text":"and you can see, they really like that."},{"time":706000,"text":"They become very energetic, and able"},{"time":708000,"text":"to find the resource in the environment,"},{"time":710000,"text":"similar to what we saw before."},{"time":712000,"text":"But again, these are done in these primordial"},{"time":714000,"text":"conditions, really messy conditions,"},{"time":716000,"text":"not sort of sterile laboratory conditions."},{"time":718000,"text":"These are very dirty little protocells,"},{"time":720000,"text":"as a matter of fact. (Laughter)"},{"time":722000,"text":"But they have lifelike properties, is the point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"So, doing these artificial life experiments"},{"time":728000,"text":"helps us define a potential path between"},{"time":731000,"text":"non-living and living systems."},{"time":734000,"text":"And not only that, but it helps us"},{"time":736000,"text":"broaden our view of what life is"},{"time":738000,"text":"and what possible life there could be"},{"time":740000,"text":"out there -- life that could be very different"},{"time":742000,"text":"from life that we find here on Earth."},{"time":745000,"text":"And that leads me to the next"},{"time":747000,"text":"term, which is \"weird life.\""},{"time":749000,"text":"This is a term by Steve Benner."},{"time":752000,"text":"This is used in reference to a report"},{"time":754000,"text":"in 2007 by the National Research Council"},{"time":756000,"text":"in the United States, wherein"},{"time":758000,"text":"they tried to understand how we can"},{"time":760000,"text":"look for life elsewhere in the universe, okay,"},{"time":762000,"text":"especially if that life is very different from life"},{"time":764000,"text":"on Earth. If we went to another planet and"},{"time":767000,"text":"we thought there might be life there,"},{"time":769000,"text":"how could we even recognize it as life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"Well, they came up with three very general"},{"time":773000,"text":"criteria. First is -- and they're listed here."},{"time":775000,"text":"The first is, the system has to be in"},{"time":777000,"text":"non-equilibrium. That means the system"},{"time":779000,"text":"cannot be dead, in a matter of fact."},{"time":780000,"text":"Basically what that means is, you have"},{"time":782000,"text":"an input of energy into the system that life"},{"time":784000,"text":"can use and exploit to maintain itself."},{"time":787000,"text":"This is similar to having the Sun shining"},{"time":789000,"text":"on the Earth, driving photosynthesis,"},{"time":791000,"text":"driving the ecosystem."},{"time":793000,"text":"Without the Sun, there's likely to be"},{"time":795000,"text":"no life on this planet."},{"time":797000,"text":"Secondly, life needs to be in liquid form,"},{"time":799000,"text":"so that means even if we had some"},{"time":801000,"text":"interesting structures, interesting molecules"},{"time":803000,"text":"together but they were frozen solid,"},{"time":805000,"text":"then this is not a good place for life."},{"time":807000,"text":"And thirdly, we need to be able to make"},{"time":809000,"text":"and break chemical bonds. And again"},{"time":811000,"text":"this is important because life transforms"},{"time":813000,"text":"resources from the environment into"},{"time":815000,"text":"building blocks so it can maintain itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"Now today, I told you about very strange"},{"time":819000,"text":"and weird protocells -- some that contain clay,"},{"time":821000,"text":"some that have primordial ooze in them,"},{"time":824000,"text":"some that have basically oil"},{"time":826000,"text":"instead of water inside of them."},{"time":828000,"text":"Most of these don't contain DNA,"},{"time":830000,"text":"but yet they have lifelike properties."},{"time":832000,"text":"But these protocells satisfy"},{"time":835000,"text":"these general requirements of living systems."},{"time":838000,"text":"So by making these chemical, artificial"},{"time":840000,"text":"life experiments, we hope not only"},{"time":842000,"text":"to understand something fundamental"},{"time":844000,"text":"about the origin of life and the existence"},{"time":846000,"text":"of life on this planet, but also"},{"time":848000,"text":"what possible life there could be"},{"time":850000,"text":"out there in the universe. Thank you."},{"time":853000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}